doc.previous: The Royal Flying Doctor Service of Australia previously operated a large number of 90 Series King Airs but retired the last example in 2006 standardizing on the King Air 200 Series and the Pilatus PC 12 for its fleet requirements
doc.after: A total of more than 3 100 King Air 90 and 100 series aircraft have been delivered as of August 2008 48
